target_id: This module defines debt securities contracts both cash and synthetic, such as bonds, structured finance instruments, short term or money market instruments, and other contracts characterized by the holding of some debt of the issuer or primary party by the holder or counterparty.
Financial Industry Business Ontology (FIBO) Securities and Equities (SEC) Debt Module

The SEC Debt Module covers content specific to debt instruments, including but not limited to bonds and asset-backed securities. This ontology provides metadata about the Debt module and its contents.
Office of Financial Research (US Dept of the Treasury)
